    <remarks variants="7">
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Foreign Service Officer. Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Peru); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Guatemala); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Grenada); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Argentina); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Barbados).</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/people/ortiz-francis-vincent</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Officer in Charge of Spanish Affairs, Bureau of European Affairs, Department of State, until August 1966</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1964-68v12/persons#p_OFVJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Deputy Chief of Mission of the Embassy in Uruguay until 1973; Country Director for Argentina, Uruguay, and Paraguay, Bureau of Inter-American Affairs, Department of State, 1973–1975; Deputy Executive Secretary of the Department of State, 1975–1977</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76v38p2/persons#p_OFV_1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Deputy Chief of Mission, U.S. Embassy in Uruguay, from September 1973; Country Director for Argentina, Paraguay, and Uruguay, until 1975</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve11p2/persons#p_OFV_1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Deputy Executive Secretary, Executive Secretariat, Department of State</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve14p1/persons#p_OFV1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Deputy Executive Secretary of the Department of State; thereafter, Ambassador to Barbados and Grenada from July 29, 1977, until May 15, 1979; Ambassador to Guatemala from July 17, 1979, until August 6, 1980</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1977-80v02/persons#p_OFV_1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Ambassador to Peru from October 1, 1981, until October 27, 1983; Ambassador to Argentina from November 18, 1983</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1981-88v13/persons#p_OFV_1</source-url>
        </remark>
